{title: A Toast To The Bride}
{artist: Stonewall Jackson}
{composer: Written by Steve Karliski}

[C]Today's the day to [G7]laugh and shout
While those wedding [C]bells ring out
And don't mind me if [F]teardrops start
You [G7]see I'm in mourning for my broken [C]heart
Drink drink a [G7]toast to the bride
Drink to the man at her [C]side
Then bow your heads in [F]sympathy
One [C]minute of silence [F]in memory
Of a [C]love that has died and [F]never can [C]be
A new love's born and old love [G7]dies
His heart rejoices [C]my heart cries
He starts a life of [F]wedded bliss
[G7]While I cry my life away in loneli[C]ness
Repeat #2
Congratulate them [G7]man and wife
Wish them both a [C]happy life
Then help me lose this [F]misery
And [G7]say something nice to comfort [C]me
Repeat #2 x2